@liveresume So you turned out to be right. There were a couple of issues at play. First, the `MatchWithFade` code in the example was taken verbatim from the RR folks, so I assumed it was entirely right. Second, I didn't fully comprehend the issue with keys that you were suggesting. Somebody posted a note to the SO thread that clarified things for me:

http://stackoverflow.com/questions/41388263/nested-match-routes-with-react-router-v4-and-matchwithfade

The summary is that each key has to be unique to the `Match` instance and cannot change on re-renders, which means a random number generator is no good. The guy on SO suggested using `rest.pattern` from RR, which is the part of the URL pattern that matches up to the current `Match`, which strikes me as exactly the right value to use for the key. So, sorry for the kerfuffle, and thanks for your help!

